            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Two months back I visited this school for admission for my son in 1st grade. Here I have to mention that my son is mild autistic. He is verbal communicates his needs and can do well in academics but he lacks social skills. I informed about this on the very first day when I came with my son. School admission coordinator sowjanya pointed out at my son's speech. I told her about this problem. She replied me that she needs an assessment report about his issue. I was ok with that but she mentioned that assessment should be done in ICGC suggested by school counselor. I don't know about the process in DPS so I agreed to whatever they demanded.I went to that clinic and they did assessment to my son. They gave me report on plain paper without any letter head of the clinic. Next day (3rd time) again I went to school made my son write the admission test. Eventhough he is special kid he wrote all the papers English, maths, Telugu, Hindi. He didn't leave anything. We gave our answer sheets back and left but then I remembered that I visited school for 3 times but not even once I was given fee structure. That's how a special parent was treated by sowjanya. In the evening sowjanya called me to inform that they are willing to give admission only when I hire shadow teacher for my son. That is going to be an extra 1.5 lakh added to original fee. I spent almost 7000 for the assessment and travel atlast I was told that because my son is special I need to pay extra amount to shadow teacher. CBSE schools should never deny the admission of any special kid. Every CBSE school should have an special educator. When I asked about this I was not given proper answer. I don't recommend this school even to normal kid parents.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
